<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="186" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,672,974,996]" box="[151,672,974,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Xue &amp; Zhang, 2018" authorityName="Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[294,584,974,996]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lambirocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cycloformulus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[294,584,974,996]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Lambirocerus cycloformulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[591,672,975,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[591,672,975,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1041,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
Robust, ochraceous. Head wider than pronotum. Coronal suture absent, crown finely rugose, with median length slightly longer than length next to eyes. Face slightly wider than long; lateral frontal sutures short, straight, not reaching ocelli; ocelli closer to midline than to corresponding eye and near midheight of eye in facial view; gena with straight lateral margin, not incised below eye; lorum broad; rostrum not reaching hind coxae; anteclypeus surpassing apex of gena, apex wider than base, lateral margin straight (
<figureCitation box="[977,1068,1185,1210]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1557,1579]" captionTargetBox="[159,1419,888,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,878,1533]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face; E, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439986/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum shagreen, declivous anteriorly, 2.8 times wider than long. Combined length of mesoscutum and scutellum longer than pronotum, median sulcus obviously angulate. Forewing with 4 apical and 2 subapical cells, r-m1 and m-cu1 crossveins present, outer apical cell largest, adjacent apical cell smallest and parallel sided; clavus with two veins; appendix broad and extended to wing apex, bordering inner two apical cells (
<figureCitation box="[924,1011,1329,1354]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1557,1579]" captionTargetBox="[159,1419,888,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,878,1533]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face; E, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439986/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Fore femur with few short and fine setae. Fore tibia with several stout and long AV and PV setae on distal half, fine setae on basal half. Hind tibia with 19–20 setae on row PD, 6 setae on AD and 6 setae on apical half of AV. Hind femur with 2+1 apical setae. Hind basitarsus with two platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1041,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
Male genitalia. Male pygofer dorsal margin with broad basal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1120,1473,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[169,1388,202,1534]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1414,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, apex of pygofer, posterior view; C, connective, ventral view; D, connective, lateral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; H, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; I, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439994/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Segment X unsclerotized; sclerotized basal collar absent. Connective slender, I-shaped, stem longer than combined width of arms, median anterior lobe acute (
<figureCitation box="[373,461,1545,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[169,1388,202,1534]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1414,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, apex of pygofer, posterior view; C, connective, ventral view; D, connective, lateral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; H, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; I, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439994/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Style well-developed, apophysis short and stout, curved at right angle relative to base, with lamelliform lateral lobe at bend (
<figureCitation box="[591,672,1581,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[169,1388,202,1534]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1414,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, apex of pygofer, posterior view; C, connective, ventral view; D, connective, lateral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; H, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; I, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439994/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
Fig. 
<date box="[646,672,1582,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">4I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft long and slender, attenuated in lateral view, apex bifurcate in posterior view; gonopore subapical on ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[903,1036,1617,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[169,1388,202,1534]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1414,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lambirocerus cycloformulus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, apex of pygofer, posterior view; C, connective, ventral view; D, connective, lateral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, apex of aedeagus, ventral view; H, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; I, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439994/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Figs. 4E–H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
